Meet Our Team
STEVE WEBSTER, SENIOR PASTOR
Pastor Steve Webster
and his wife
Christa, along with their three children, Megan, Caleb,
Caleb, and
Isaiah, were led by God to join the family at First Baptist Church of Bushnell in 2025.
Pastor Steve accepted Christ and was baptized at a young age, setting the foundation for his involvement in ministry. Throughout his career, he has served in various pastoral roles, including serving as a youth pastor, outreach pastor, church planter, and senior pastor.
He is a graduate of Liberty, and remains committed to ongoing education and growth, regularly participating in education focused on church planting, revitalization, and evangelism.
In his personal life, Pastor Steve enjoys outdoor activities like fishing and hunting. Heâs also an avid Florida Gator fan. Above all, Pastor Steve has a deep passion for preaching God's Word and sharing the Good News of Jesus Christ with others. He welcomes you to come and be a part of what God is doing at First Baptist Bushnell.
Paul Paisley - Discipleship, Family, & Student Pastor
Paul joined the church staff in March 2019 as the Student Pastor. He and his wife Hillary were married in 2007 and they have 3 children: Micah, Caleb, and Elizabeth. Before entering full-time ministry, Paul served 5 years in the US NAVY. Paul received his BA in Ministry from The Baptist College of Florida, and his Master of Divinity from Liberty University. Paul is passionate about reaching and discipling students and their parents. He and Hillary have served churches in Florida and Alabama since 2008. One of Paul's favorite verses is Proverbs 3:5-6 "Trust in the Lord with all your heart; do not depend on your own understanding. Seek His will in all you do and He will show you the path to take."
DOUG JOHNSON -
Minister of Worship
Doug was called as Worship
Pastor to FBC of Bushnell on February 15
th
2024. He hails from the
Volunteer State of Tennessee (GO BIG ORANGE!), is a US Army Veteran, and has
been in ministry since 2009. He has been happily married to his wife and best friend
Kellie since 1999. Together they have a son and daughter. Their son Preston is
married to their wonderful daughter-in-law, Ashley, who together now have a
precious daughter of their own, Addie Mae. Doug and Kellieâs daughter, Kirsten,
just graduated nursing school and is getting married to her fiancÃ©, Kaleb
Kinney in November 2024.
Doug loves serving the
Lord and is passionate about leading our congregation in praise and worship and
sharing the life-saving, life-changing Gospel of Jesus Christ.
Elizabeth Babiloni - Children's Director
Bio coming soon.
Judy Wells - Church Secretary
Judy is the welcoming voice who greets you at the door or on the phone.  She has been on staff since May 2015.
Judy Foote - Financial Secretary
Judy is the part time Financial Secretary and has been on staff since September 2003.
Wendy Stevens - Custodial Manager
As the long-time Custodial Manager, Wendy oversees and assists with maintaining the cleanliness of the church facilities. Wendy is a joyful servant of the Lord who always has a ready smile and cheerful word for all who encounter her.
Josh Stevens - Custodial Staff
Josh has been a faithful member of our custodial staff for many years. He regularly maintains the day-to-day cleanliness of the church facilities. Although Josh is on the quiet side, his love for the Lord shines brightly through all that he puts his hands to.
